e, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Henry Scott was born in 1279, in Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Sir Henry Scott - Third Lord of Balweary in 1300, in Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1279–":"1279–Surnud","1275–1330":"1275–1330","1315–1355":"1315–1355","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1355":"1355","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland","Balwearie Castle, Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1279–":"1279–Kuollut","1275–1330":"1275–1330","1315–1355":"1315–1355","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1355":"1355","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland","Balwearie Castle, Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1279–":"1279–Décédée","1275–1330":"1275–1330","1315–1355":"1315–1355","1279–Female":"1279–Décédée","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1355":"1355","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Écosse","Balwearie Castle, Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Henry Scott est née en 1279, à Kirkcaldy, Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Sir Henry Scott - Third Lord of Balweary en 1300, à Kirkcaldy, Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1279–":"1